      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002790
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-01T12:51:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The key is (MessageType, CommandCode), which means only one pending long-running request per command type is supported. If the  same command is sent twice (e.g., from polling), the second registerResponseHandler fails with EEXIST. Consider adding instanceId to the key:\nusing ResponseKey \u003d std::tuple\u003cgpu::MessageType, uint8_t /*commandCode*/, uint8_t /*instanceId*/\u003e;\nThe instanceId is available in the long-running event payload (decoded by decodeLongRunningResponseEvent), so the handler can\n  still match it on the event side. This would allow multiple concurrent long-running requests for the same command to coexist.",
      "parentUuid": "ad9ef1ea_384d70b7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 34,
        "endChar": 62
      },
